Atty Kaehne stands by objections made on the record as to bindover. Specifically that two threatening email communications as directed to victim 1 were not made. Course of conduct was not directed at a single person, but to multiple different people - does not meet requirements as to statute.
State notes that Officer testified to May 7th and May 18th emails directed at victim 1.
Court - based on testimony at Preliminary Hearing, cannot find probable cause to bindover for Felony. Count 1 Dismissed.
